&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Brief Description of the Role: &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to appoint an enthusiastic and competent multi-skilled technician with ability to diagnose and repair faults on plant and equipment in accordance with relevant standards and operational procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Summary of most important Experience/Skills/Qualifications required:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have served a recognised electrical apprenticeship, and have completed a multi-skilling training course or have appropriate multi-skilled experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Informal Enquiries to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mr Paul Noble, Estates Manager, Estates Department, Bradford Royal Infirmary, &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tel: 01274 384684.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer staff gymnasiums on both hospital sites, excellent pension scheme and advice on childcare.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 18.11.20 (This date may change dependent on the response)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
